  "prompt": "What is average cost per couple to travel Bhutan from AHMEDABAD?",
  "response": "The average cost for a couple to travel to Bhutan from Ahmedabad can vary widely depending on several factors, including the mode of travel, duration of stay, type of accommodation, and activities planned. Here\u2019s a general breakdown to give you an idea:\n\n### 1. **Flights:**\n   - **Round-trip airfare:** Flights from Ahmedabad to Paro (Bhutan\u2019s international airport) typically range from **\u20b925,000 to \u20b945,000 per person**, depending on the season and airline. For a couple, this could be around **\u20b950,000 to \u20b990,000**.\n\n### 2. **Bhutan Daily Tariff:**\n   - Bhutan imposes a **minimum daily tariff** for tourists, which includes accommodation, meals, transportation, and a guide. As of 2023:\n     - **\u20b97,000 to \u20b98,000 per person per day** during the high season (March to May, September to November).\n     - **\u20b95,500 to \u20b96,500 per person per day** during the low season (December to February, June to August).\n   - For a couple, this translates to approximately **\u20b914,000 to \u20b916,000 per day** in high season and **\u20b911,000 to \u20b913,000 per day** in low season.\n\n### 3. **Visa Fees:**\n   - The Bhutan visa fee is **\u20b91,200 per person**, so for a couple, it would be **\u20b92,400**.\n\n### 4. **Other Costs:**\n   - **Travel Insurance:** \u20b91,000 to \u20b92,000 per person.\n   - **Souvenirs, shopping, and extra activities:** \u20b95,000 to \u20b915,000 depending on preferences.\n\n### **Estimated Total Cost:**\nFor a **7-day trip**:\n   - High Season: \u20b950,000 (flights) + \u20b9112,000 (tariff) + \u20b92,400 (visa) + \u20b915,000 (extras) = **\u20b91,79,400**.\n   - Low Season: \u20b950,000 (flights) + \u20b984,000 (tariff) + \u20b92,400 (visa) + \u20b915,000 (extras) = **\u20b91,51,400**.\n\nFor a **10-day trip**:\n   - High Season: \u20b950,000 (flights) + \u20b9112,000 (tariff) + \u20b92,400 (visa) + \u20b915,000 (extras) = **\u20b92,02,400**.\n   - Low Season: \u20b950,000 (flights) + \u20b984,000 (tariff) + \u20b92,400 (visa) + \u20b915,000 (extras) = **\u20b91,74,400**.\n\n### Note:\n- These are approximate costs and can vary based on your choices.\n- Indian nationals traveling to Bhutan by road do not have to pay the daily tariff, but you\u2019ll need to arrange your own accommodation and transport. Flights are still required if traveling by air. \n\nIt\u2019s best to plan in advance and consult a travel agent for the latest rates and packages.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
